WEBVTT

00:01.902 --> 00:02.970
1979--CONGRESS
AUTHORIZED THE FORMATION

00:03.003 --> 00:05.406
OF A CONTINGENT OF ELITE
SPECIAL FORCES SOLDIERS

00:05.439 --> 00:07.075
WHO ANSWER ONLY
TO THE PRESIDENT

00:07.108 --> 00:08.342
OF THE UNITED STATES.

00:08.376 --> 00:10.344
THEIR MISSIONS,
AND THEIR VERY EXISTENCE,

00:10.378 --> 00:12.913
ARE CLOSELY GUARDED SECRETS

00:12.946 --> 00:14.382
PROTECTED BY
THE SOLDIERS THEMSELVES,

00:14.415 --> 00:15.516
AND THEIR WIVES

00:15.549 --> 00:16.984
WHO POSSESS SECRETS
OF THEIR OWN.

00:17.017 --> 00:18.018
YOU DO NOT TELL
YOUR MOTHER,

00:18.052 --> 00:20.854
YOUR BEST FRIEND,
YOUR PRIEST--

00:20.888 --> 00:22.256
WHAT YOUR HUSBAND DOES.

00:22.290 --> 00:23.357
ARMY REGULATIONS STATE--

00:23.391 --> 00:24.558
YOU AREN'T IN THE ARMY.

00:24.592 --> 00:25.593
YOU'RE IN THE UNIT.

00:25.626 --> 00:27.095
PREVIOUSLY ON THE UNIT--

00:27.128 --> 00:29.763
WE HAVE AN IMMEDIATE NEED
FOR A DRIVER IN BRAZIL.

00:29.797 --> 00:33.401
BLACKTHORN WILL
GIVE YOU THE OPPORTUNITY
TO TRAVEL,

00:33.434 --> 00:34.268
SEE THE WORLD.

00:34.302 --> 00:35.769
NON-COMBAT ZONE PAY

00:35.803 --> 00:37.271
IS $1,500 A WEEK,
STARTING.

00:37.305 --> 00:39.273
[TIRES SQUEALING]

00:39.307 --> 00:40.941
KID'S ALMOST
READY FOR THE JOB.

00:40.974 --> 00:42.410
GLAD TO HEAR IT.

00:42.443 --> 00:44.978
WELCOME TO THE FAMILY.

00:47.815 --> 00:51.652
COME ON...YOU CAN
DO BETTER THAN THAT.

00:53.487 --> 00:55.789
[BEEPS]

00:55.823 --> 00:57.358
[BEEPING]

00:57.391 --> 01:00.861
[WHIRRING AND CLICKING]

01:00.894 --> 01:02.796
[BANGS]

01:10.971 --> 01:12.240
ALLENDE? NORIEGA?

01:12.273 --> 01:15.309
NO EMBROIDERY.
WOULD BE MY PICK, TOO.

01:16.244 --> 01:17.211
DON'T NEED A BELT.

01:17.245 --> 01:20.614
OH, TAKE IT--
KEEP YOUR PANTS ON.

01:20.648 --> 01:21.549
GET IN THE CASH?

01:21.582 --> 01:23.217
IS A PIG'S
PORKER PINK?

01:23.251 --> 01:24.118
YOU TELL ME?

01:24.152 --> 01:26.954
SMALL BILLS, MANILA
ENVELOPE, IN YOUR BAG.

01:26.987 --> 01:29.323
GRACIAS.

01:32.025 --> 01:34.795
CREDIT CARDS,
GUYANA DRIVER'S LICENSE,

01:34.828 --> 01:36.130
BUSINESS CARDS.

01:36.164 --> 01:37.165
ROHAN?

01:37.198 --> 01:39.800
WHY NOT? MEXICO CITY,
CONNECT TO GUYANA,

01:39.833 --> 01:43.537
AND GROUND TRAVEL
ACROSS THE BORDER.

01:43.804 --> 01:45.839
CONTACT IN SAN-TOMÁS?
YES.

01:45.873 --> 01:48.108
BEV?
WHAT?

01:48.142 --> 01:50.010
WHO'S MY LIAISON?

01:51.845 --> 01:53.681
AGENCY. LOCAL HIRE.

01:53.714 --> 01:54.648
AGENCY? COME ON.

01:54.682 --> 01:55.816
I JUST PREP 'EM.
I DON'T PICK 'EM.

01:55.849 --> 01:58.352
IF THEY WANT POISON PENS
AND EXPLODING SEASHELLS...

01:58.386 --> 02:00.354
YEAH. ALL YOU NEED IS
THE 2 HANDS THAT GOD GAVE YOU.

02:00.388 --> 02:01.455
I'M JUST SAYIN'.

02:01.489 --> 02:02.923
OH, YOU'RE SO BEAUTIFUL
WHEN YOU'RE ANGRY.

02:02.956 --> 02:04.792
WELL, I'M BEAUTIFUL
BECAUSE MY SOUL
IS BEAUTIFUL.

02:04.825 --> 02:06.093
AND IF MY SOUL
WERE NOT BEAUTIFUL,

02:06.126 --> 02:07.628
THIS MAGNIFICENT FACE
AND BODY

02:07.661 --> 02:10.097
WOULD BE BUT
AN UNATTRACTIVE HUSK.

02:10.130 --> 02:10.998
UH-HUH.

02:11.031 --> 02:12.800
UH--YOUR RING.

02:12.833 --> 02:14.635
RIGHT.

02:15.703 --> 02:17.838
I'LL BRING YOU BACK
A SOUVENIR.

02:17.871 --> 02:18.706
OK.

02:18.739 --> 02:20.908
HASTA LUEGO.
BYE.

02:28.216 --> 02:30.984
"3 ADDITIONAL TALIBAN
SAFE HOUSES NEAR KANDAHAR

02:31.018 --> 02:34.388
"WERE NEUTRALIZED BY UNIT
OPERATORS IN THIS OPERATION.

02:34.422 --> 02:37.858
A.I.C. HAS IDENTIFIED NEW
SUPPLY LINES TO INSURGENT--"

02:37.891 --> 02:42.696
EXCUSE ME, COLONEL RYAN,
UH, WE HAVE YOUR REPORT
BEFORE US--

02:42.730 --> 02:43.697
VERY COMPREHENSIVE.

02:43.731 --> 02:46.634
I WANT TO ASK YOU
ABOUT LATIN AMERICA.

02:46.667 --> 02:49.303
IS YOUR UNIT PLANNING
A MISSION THERE NOW?

02:49.337 --> 02:52.240
[INDISTINCT WHISPERING]

02:54.107 --> 02:57.911
WE ALWAYS HAVE
VARIOUS MISSIONS
IN THE PLANNING STAGES

02:57.945 --> 02:59.913
DIRECTED TOWARDS
VARIOUS AREAS

02:59.947 --> 03:01.382
INCLUDING LATIN AMERICA.

03:01.415 --> 03:03.251
THIS IS
A SECURE CHAMBER.

03:03.284 --> 03:04.718
SIR, THE AGENDA
FOR THIS BRIEFING IS--

03:04.752 --> 03:06.987
IS COUNTERTERRORISM.
AND AFGHANISTAN.

03:07.020 --> 03:08.989
THAT'S YOUR AGENDA.
MY QUESTION THEN HAS TO DO--

03:09.022 --> 03:11.225
CONGRESSMAN GELBER,
I'M SURE I CAN ANSWER
ANY QUESTIONS--

03:11.259 --> 03:13.527
MR. KRINSMAN, ARE YOU HERE
AS WHITE HOUSE COUNSEL

03:13.561 --> 03:14.728
OR WHITE HOUSE MUZZLE?

03:14.762 --> 03:17.331
ARE YOU DEPLOYING
A HIT TEAM TO LATIN AMERICA

03:17.365 --> 03:21.669
TO ASSASSINATE
A CERTAIN OIL MINISTER,
A MR. LUIS INEZ REALE?

03:21.702 --> 03:25.072
CONGRESSMAN GELBER,
IF THIS COMMITTEE WOULD
LIKE OUR AGENDA

03:25.105 --> 03:26.874
TO INCLUDE OPERATIONS
IN LATIN AMERICA,

03:26.907 --> 03:29.009
YOU CAN SUBMIT
YOUR REQUEST
TO MY OFFICE.

03:29.042 --> 03:29.743
I'LL BE HAPPY TO--

03:29.777 --> 03:30.778
OH, I'VE BEEN
TRYING FOR MONTHS

03:30.811 --> 03:33.281
TO GET AN ANSWER
OUT OF YOUR BOSS,
MR. KRINSMAN.

03:33.314 --> 03:34.682
BUT THE VICE PRESIDENT
APPARENTLY MAINTAINS

03:34.715 --> 03:38.118
THAT CONGRESSIONAL OVERSIGHT
IS AN ARCANE NOTION.

03:38.151 --> 03:40.754
COLONEL RYAN,
RIGHT AFTER 9/11

03:40.788 --> 03:45.092
THE PRESIDENT EXPANDED
YOUR AUTHORITY TO TARGET
PARTICULAR INDIVIDUALS.

03:45.125 --> 03:45.859
IS THAT CORRECT?

03:45.893 --> 03:48.296
ARE WE SPEAKING OF
TERRORISTS, SIR?

03:48.329 --> 03:50.097
THAT WAS MY QUESTION.

03:50.130 --> 03:54.768
DO YOU BELIEVE
LOUIS INEZ REALE
IS A TERRORIST?

03:57.571 --> 03:59.106
I HAVE NEVER
MET THE MAN, SIR.

03:59.139 --> 04:03.477
MR. REALE OVERSEES
THE SUPPLY OF 130 MILLION
BARRELS OF CRUDE

04:03.511 --> 04:05.112
TO THE U.S. EACH YEAR.

04:05.145 --> 04:07.715
AS OIL MINISTER,
HE HAS BEEN MAKING SOME NOISE

04:07.748 --> 04:10.618
ABOUT SHUTTING DOWN
U.S. OPERATIONS
IN HIS COUNTRY.

04:10.651 --> 04:11.819
DOES THAT MAKE HIM
A TERRORIST?

04:11.852 --> 04:14.087
WITH RESPECT, SIR,
THESE QUESTIONS
ARE OUTSIDE MY PURVIEW.

04:14.121 --> 04:18.959
I'M JUST ASKING IF MR. REALE
IS CONSIDERED A THREAT
TO THE UNITED STATES.

04:18.992 --> 04:20.961
CONGRESSMAN GELBERT,
THESE QUESTIONS
ARE INAPPROPRIATE.

04:20.994 --> 04:23.964
ARE YOU UNDER ORDERS
TO ASSASSINATE MR. REALE?!

04:23.997 --> 04:25.132
WITH ALL
DUE RESPECT, SIR--

04:25.165 --> 04:28.602
HANG DUE RESPECT, COLONEL.

04:29.537 --> 04:31.939
I'D LIKE SOME ANSWERS.

04:32.606 --> 04:34.308
SIR, MY JOB
AND THE JOB OF MY MEN

04:34.342 --> 04:37.277
IS TO PROTECT
AND DEFEND THE INTERESTS
OF THIS COUNTRY

04:37.311 --> 04:39.480
AS DETERMINED BY
THE EXECUTIVE BRANCH.

04:39.513 --> 04:42.115
IT IS NOT MY JOB TO MAKE
NOR TO INFLUENCE POLICY.

04:42.149 --> 04:45.185
IF YOU DISAGREE
WITH SPECIFIC
MISSION OBJECTIVES,

04:45.218 --> 04:47.621
I STRONGLY SUGGEST YOU
ADDRESS YOUR CONCERNS

04:47.655 --> 04:49.256
TO SOMEONE HIGHER
IN THE CHAIN OF COMMAND.

04:49.289 --> 04:53.293
THEN WHAT YOU'RE SAYING IS
YOU'RE JUST GOING TO SIT THERE
ALL AFTERNOON AND STONEWALL.

04:53.327 --> 04:56.029
FRANKLY, SIR,
YES, SIR, I AM, SIR.

04:56.630 --> 05:00.501
[CARIBBEAN MUSIC PLAYING]

05:33.066 --> 05:36.036
[BAND SINGING IN SPANISH]

05:38.572 --> 05:41.642
SWEETHEART,
I'M SO SORRY!

05:41.675 --> 05:44.311
I KNOW I'M LATE,
ROHAN, BUT...

05:44.344 --> 05:49.483
THERE WERE THESE SHOES.

05:49.517 --> 05:54.688
REALE SENT HIS DRIVER.
HIS TERMS.

05:57.958 --> 06:00.428
I SEE.

06:00.461 --> 06:02.596
OOH, WHAT A THOUGHTFUL
HUSBAND.

06:02.630 --> 06:04.064
HMM.

06:04.765 --> 06:06.900
WE SHOULD GO THEN.

06:07.635 --> 06:09.637
I'M WITH YOU!

06:16.276 --> 06:18.912
OH, MY...

06:19.780 --> 06:21.114
* FIRED UP
* FIRED UP

06:21.148 --> 06:22.282
* FIRED UP
* FIRED UP

06:22.315 --> 06:23.451
* PLENTY SUN
* PLENTY SUN

06:23.484 --> 06:24.452
* FIRED UP
* FIRED UP

06:24.485 --> 06:25.619
* HERE WE GO
* HERE WE GO

06:25.653 --> 06:26.887
* ON THE ROAD
* ON THE ROAD

06:26.920 --> 06:28.088
* PLENTY SUN
* PLENTY SUN

06:28.121 --> 06:29.222
* FIRED UP
* FIRED UP

06:29.256 --> 06:30.390
* FIRED UP
* FIRED UP

06:30.424 --> 06:32.125
* FIRED UP
* FIRED UP

06:32.159 --> 06:32.793
* PLENTY SUN

06:32.826 --> 06:34.895
* FIRED UP
* FIRED UP

06:36.229 --> 06:38.999
[BOOM, GUNSHOT]

07:04.525 --> 07:05.993
MR. AND MRS. GIBSON, WELCOME.

07:06.026 --> 07:09.730
I TRUST THE RIDE FROM SAN-TOMÁS
WAS NOT TOO UNPLEASANT.

07:09.763 --> 07:10.664
AN EASY DRIVE.

07:10.698 --> 07:12.099
DID HE RECITE FOR YOU?

07:12.132 --> 07:12.966
RECITE?
WHAT?

07:13.000 --> 07:14.735
YEAH, YEATS, KIPLING--
WHATEVER YOU LIKE.

07:14.768 --> 07:17.805
TRUCHA USED TO TEACH POETRY
AT THE UNIVERSITY.

07:17.838 --> 07:19.272
BEFORE THE GOVERNMENT CHANGE.

07:19.306 --> 07:21.675
HMM.
LOOK AT THIS
WONDERFUL HOME.

07:21.709 --> 07:23.777
IT BELONGED TO
AN AMERICAN CORPORATION.

07:23.811 --> 07:24.612
BANANAS?

07:24.645 --> 07:26.113
BANANAS, THEN OIL.

07:26.146 --> 07:26.847
NOW OURS.

07:26.880 --> 07:30.618
MM-HMM. OH,
A HOUSEWARMING GIFT

07:30.651 --> 07:31.785
FROM MY CLIENT.

07:31.819 --> 07:36.624
THE DUTCH ARE SUCH
A WARM AND GENEROUS
PEOPLE.

07:36.657 --> 07:38.859
AND GOOD CLIENTS
TO HAVE, I'M SURE.

07:38.892 --> 07:41.128
I HAVE CONTRACTS IN MY BAG.

07:41.161 --> 07:42.963
DRILLING RIGHTS,
BARREL QUOTAS.

07:42.996 --> 07:44.498
WE ARE BORING
YOUR BEAUTIFUL WIFE.

07:44.532 --> 07:48.168
SHE DOESN'T COME ALL THE WAY
FROM THE CITY TO LISTEN
TO SO MUCH BUSINESS TALK.

07:48.201 --> 07:49.637
AM I RIGHT, SEÑORA GIBSON?

07:49.670 --> 07:50.604
MARIANA.

07:50.638 --> 07:52.039
WE HAVE ALL WEEKEND
TO TALK BUSINESS.

07:52.072 --> 07:53.641
COME. LET ME SHOW YOU AROUND.

07:53.674 --> 07:56.877
YOU'RE NOT FROM GUYANA
LIKE YOUR HUSBAND.

07:56.910 --> 07:59.146
I GREW UP NOT FAR FROM HERE.

07:59.179 --> 08:00.180
OLIVOS.

08:00.213 --> 08:01.148
OLIVOS?!

08:01.181 --> 08:04.652
MY WIFE--REST HER SOUL--
WAS FROM OLIVOS.

08:04.685 --> 08:06.086
BEAUTIFUL ORCHARDS.

08:06.119 --> 08:11.224
BEAUTIFUL ORCHARDS.
ROHAN AND I MARRIED
AMONG THE AVOCADOS.

08:11.258 --> 08:13.326
HOW LONG AGO?
6 YEARS.

08:13.360 --> 08:14.494
6 YEARS.

08:14.528 --> 08:18.465
COME. COME. I WANT
TO HEAR ALL ABOUT YOU,
AND YOUR FAMILY,

08:18.498 --> 08:21.168
HOW YOU MET, EVERYTHING.

08:21.835 --> 08:23.303
KIPLING, HMM?

08:23.336 --> 08:27.675
"THE GREAT POET
OF THE EMPIRE."

08:33.346 --> 08:35.816
[RADIO PLAYING SPANISH MUSIC]

08:35.849 --> 08:38.085
[DING]
WORKS.

08:38.686 --> 08:40.921
SO DO YOU HAVE--
DO YOU HAVE
ANY OTHER GUESTS?

08:40.954 --> 08:42.189
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

08:42.222 --> 08:44.958
OTHERS... UNO, DOS, TRES.

08:45.626 --> 08:47.695
AH.

08:49.129 --> 08:50.798
WHAT?

08:58.706 --> 09:00.273
[SOLID THUD]

09:00.808 --> 09:05.045
IT'S, UH--
IT'S BIRD WATCHING
EQUIPMENT.

09:05.078 --> 09:08.515
IT'S FOR BIRD--
FOR, UH, FOR BIRDS.

09:08.548 --> 09:10.450
WATCHING--WATCHING
FLYING BIRDS.

09:10.483 --> 09:12.152
WATCHING BIRDS.

09:12.820 --> 09:15.555
PÁJARO. SÍ.

09:19.660 --> 09:21.428
PÁJARO.

09:23.263 --> 09:25.565
SEE. BIRDS.

09:25.599 --> 09:28.435
LIKE DUCKS.

09:29.737 --> 09:32.239
UH, KEY?
CAN I HAVE A KEY?

09:33.173 --> 09:34.975
THANK YOU.

09:35.008 --> 09:37.711
[DOOR CLOSES]

09:37.745 --> 09:39.479
[THUD]

09:50.991 --> 09:53.827
[BIRDS SQUAWKING]

09:54.862 --> 09:56.730
HEY, MANUEL,
PUT A MOVE ON.

09:56.764 --> 09:58.165
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

09:58.198 --> 10:02.636
COME ON, WE'RE MISSING
ALL THE ACTION OUT
THERE, COMPRENDE BUDDY?

10:24.858 --> 10:25.793
NICE.

10:25.826 --> 10:30.063
NEXT TIME,
I'LL BE MANUEL.

10:31.464 --> 10:33.500
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

11:36.463 --> 11:39.266
BOB AND JUDY MAGNUSON
WILL BE THERE,

11:39.299 --> 11:42.269
THE MYERS, AND OF COURSE
THE CLARKSONS.

11:42.302 --> 11:46.439
UGH, I HEAR DANA'S MISERABLE
SINCE RICK STARTED AT D.O.D.

11:46.473 --> 11:51.444
TOO MUCH ENTERTAINING.
"BOO HOO BETTY."

11:51.478 --> 11:52.579
DO I KNOW 'EM?

11:52.612 --> 11:55.182
YOU MET THEM
AT THE R.N.C. DINNER
AT MY FATHER'S TABLE.

11:55.215 --> 11:56.716
OLD FAT GUY,
REAL SUIT.

11:56.750 --> 11:59.052
REAL SUIT,
REAL INFLUENCE.

11:59.086 --> 12:02.222
MMM. LET'S STAY IN TONIGHT
AND ORDER ROOM SERVICE.

12:02.255 --> 12:03.723
YOU'RE VERY ATTRACTIVE.

12:03.757 --> 12:04.792
I'M SERIOUS.

12:04.825 --> 12:06.726
I CAN TELL.

12:07.260 --> 12:08.295
[SIGHS]

12:08.328 --> 12:11.398
SO GREAT TO SEE YOU
BACK IN YOUR ELEMENT.

12:11.431 --> 12:15.168
YOU'VE GOT THAT FIRE
BACK IN YOUR EYES.

12:20.073 --> 12:21.141
OH, LOOK AT THE TIME!

12:21.174 --> 12:22.409
IT'S WASHINGTON.

12:22.442 --> 12:24.277
LET'S BE FASHIONABLY LATE.

12:24.311 --> 12:27.680
WELL, IF YOU PUT IT
THAT WAY...

12:30.583 --> 12:32.920
HA HA HA.

12:35.823 --> 12:37.825
* DON'T TELL MY HEART

12:37.858 --> 12:38.926
* MY ACHY BREAKY HEART

12:38.959 --> 12:43.096
* I JUST DON'T THINK
HE'LL UNDERSTAND *

12:43.130 --> 12:45.298
* 'CAUSE IF YOU TELL
MY HEART *

12:45.332 --> 12:47.067
* MY ACHY BREAKY HEART

12:47.100 --> 12:50.570
* HE MIGHT BLOW UP
AND KILL THIS MAN *

12:50.603 --> 12:53.473
* WHOO

12:53.506 --> 12:55.675
MOLLY!

12:55.708 --> 12:56.910
WHOO!

12:56.944 --> 12:59.046
WHOO!

13:00.347 --> 13:03.150
YOU WERE AWESOME!

13:03.183 --> 13:04.451
IF MY HUSBAND EVER SAW...

13:04.484 --> 13:05.986
WHO CARES? YOU GOT UP THERE.

13:06.019 --> 13:07.921
MAKING A DAMNED FOOL
OF MYSELF.

13:07.955 --> 13:09.122
THERE'S NOTHING WRONG
WITH THAT.

13:09.156 --> 13:11.859
GIRLS NIGHT OUT.
LADY NEEDS TO HAVE
A LITTLE FUN.

13:11.892 --> 13:14.361
THIS LADY NEEDS
ANOTHER ROUND.
I'M BUYING.

13:14.394 --> 13:15.795
YOU BOUGHT THE LAST 2.

13:15.829 --> 13:17.297
AND I'LL GET
THE NEXT 2 IF I WANT.

13:17.330 --> 13:18.999
MY MAN IS MAKING MONEY.

13:19.032 --> 13:21.468
THANK YOU, BLACKTHORN,
THANK YOU, MOLLY.

13:21.501 --> 13:22.369
DON'T BE SILLY.

13:22.402 --> 13:23.470
WANT TO SEE SILLY?
HA HA.

13:23.503 --> 13:25.605
ANOTHER BEER,
I'M GOING TO SING

13:25.638 --> 13:28.041
THE STAR SPANGLED
BAZANGLE.

13:28.075 --> 13:30.677
NOW I GOTTA BE WITNESS
TO THIS.

13:30.710 --> 13:33.847
I BETTER PROVIDE COVER.

13:39.252 --> 13:40.287
ISN'T IT GETTING LATE?

13:40.320 --> 13:42.522
I'M FINE. I GOTTA AN HOUR
TILL THE BABYSITTER'S OFF.

13:42.555 --> 13:44.157
I WAS THINKING
ABOUT CRYSTAL.

13:44.191 --> 13:46.793
IT'S OK.
I'M HER DESIGNATED.

13:46.826 --> 13:49.262
NO CAFFEINE EVEN.

13:52.199 --> 13:54.001
WILD THING!

13:54.034 --> 13:55.702
SHE'S JUST YOUNG.

13:55.735 --> 13:58.471
EVEN AT HER AGE,
I NEVER SHOOK IT
LIKE THAT.

13:58.505 --> 14:00.573
WELL, THERE'S
STILL TIME, GIRL.

14:00.607 --> 14:03.410
GO ON.

14:09.549 --> 14:11.751
COLONEL AND
MRS. TOM RYAN.

14:11.784 --> 14:14.487
TOM, CHARLOTTE,
IT'S ABOUT TIME.

14:14.521 --> 14:15.622
HELLO.

14:15.655 --> 14:18.591
THE CABBIE GOT LOST.
THANK GOD CHARLOTTE
KNEW THE AREA.

14:18.625 --> 14:19.626
THAT'S OUR HOMETOWN GIRL.

14:19.659 --> 14:22.662
WELL, I'M SO
THRILLED TO BE BACK.
YOU'VE NO IDEA.

14:22.695 --> 14:23.863
I KNOW THE GIRLS
ALL MISSED YOU.

14:23.897 --> 14:25.532
AH. WELL, I'LL--UM--

14:25.565 --> 14:27.867
I'LL JUST--UM--
TAKE CARE OF HIM
WILL YOU?

14:27.901 --> 14:29.269
DON'T LET HIM
SULK IN A CORNER.

14:29.302 --> 14:31.939
NO WORRIES.
HE'S SAFE IN THIS COMPANY.

14:31.972 --> 14:33.941
THERE'S NO CONGRESSMEN
HIDING OUT?

14:33.974 --> 14:35.775
FORGET GELBER.
THE GUY'S EX-MARINE.

14:35.808 --> 14:37.010
THINKS SPECIAL OPS
IS HIS TURF.

14:37.044 --> 14:39.212
HEY, IF HE WANTS TO GO
HAND TO HAND WITH ME,

14:39.246 --> 14:40.914
I SHALL ACCOMMODATE HIM.

14:40.948 --> 14:42.882
I WANT YOU TO MEET
SOME OF THE WHITE HOUSE FOLKS.

14:42.916 --> 14:45.518
GOOD PEOPLE TO KNOW
WHEN AND IF.

14:45.552 --> 14:47.854
WHEN AND IF WHAT?

14:47.887 --> 14:54.227
LOOK AT HER. YOU'D THINK
SHE WAS STILL IN
THE DIPLOMATIC CORPS.

14:54.962 --> 14:56.696
YOU TWO BELONG HERE.

14:56.729 --> 14:59.099
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATION]

14:59.666 --> 15:02.069
WHERE'S THE BOURBON?

15:02.102 --> 15:04.637
HA HA HA. THIS WAY.

15:05.305 --> 15:07.107
"I WANT A DIVORCE,"

15:07.140 --> 15:09.977
AN OIL MAN SAYS
TO HIS LAWYER.

15:10.010 --> 15:14.747
"SHE IS MY WOMAN
AND SHE'S SUPPOSED
TO DO AS I SAY."

15:17.617 --> 15:21.088
DIRT DIVER,
THIS IS COOL BREEZE.
COMMO CHECK, OVER.

15:21.121 --> 15:21.955
[BEEP]

15:21.989 --> 15:23.957
AFFIRMATIVE.
WE'RE FLOATING
AND WAITING.

15:23.991 --> 15:25.092
[CLICK]

15:25.125 --> 15:27.327
THE OIL MAN REPLIES,

15:27.360 --> 15:28.495
"MAYBE NOT.

15:28.528 --> 15:32.932
BUT I DAMN WELL OUGHT TO HAVE
EXCLUSIVE DRILLING RIGHTS."

15:32.966 --> 15:34.968
[BOTH LAUGHING]

15:39.839 --> 15:43.110
BE READY.
JOB'S ABOUT TO GO DOWN.

15:47.314 --> 15:49.549
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

15:55.155 --> 15:58.425
SO MY FRIEND,
WHAT RIGHTS
ARE YOU SEEKING?

15:58.458 --> 16:01.261
MY CLIENTS WANT
THE OFFSHORE OIL FIELDS.

16:01.294 --> 16:03.296
LIGHT CRUDE.

16:03.330 --> 16:06.499
WE ARE OFFERING
$240 MILLION--

16:06.533 --> 16:09.169
NOT INCLUDING
YOUR INTEREST.

16:09.736 --> 16:12.139
8 CENTS A BARREL...

16:12.172 --> 16:13.140
TO YOUR ACCOUNT.

16:13.173 --> 16:16.009
I CAN GET MORE
FROM THE JAPANESE.

16:16.043 --> 16:17.810
[SIGHS]

16:17.844 --> 16:22.049
YOU SAY IT,
SO I MUST BELIEVE IT.

16:22.082 --> 16:24.151
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

16:24.184 --> 16:26.386
I WANT EVERYTHING.

16:26.419 --> 16:28.455
FOR TOO LONG
MY COUNTRY HAS BENT OVER

16:28.488 --> 16:30.190
FOR THE AMERICAN OIL
COMPANIES--

16:30.223 --> 16:33.226
LONG LEASES, LOW PAYOUT,
NO RESPECT.

16:33.260 --> 16:35.128
I'M GOING
TO CHANGE THAT.

16:35.162 --> 16:38.131
WE HAVE TO CONTROL
OUR OWN DESTINY.

16:38.165 --> 16:42.069
THAT MEANS CONTROLLING
THE OIL WELLS.

16:42.102 --> 16:43.803
I WILL NATIONALIZE
ALL OF THEM

16:43.836 --> 16:44.837
IF THAT'S WHAT IT TAKES.

16:44.871 --> 16:47.907
OF COURSE, WE NEED SOMEONE
TO RUN THE WELLS FOR US.

16:47.940 --> 16:52.612
BETTER YOUR DUTCH
CLIENTS THAN
THE AMERICANS.

16:53.680 --> 16:55.548
HERE WE GO.

16:55.582 --> 16:57.984
[DOGS BARKING]

16:58.017 --> 17:00.420
OH!
CHICO! BOLIVAR!

17:01.020 --> 17:04.057
SORRY, SIR.
THEY GOT OUT.

17:04.091 --> 17:05.358
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

17:05.392 --> 17:06.826
MY TWINS. HA!

17:06.859 --> 17:11.164
THEY WON'T EAT
UNLESS I FEED THEM MYSELF.

17:11.198 --> 17:12.432
QUITE SENSITIVE.

17:12.465 --> 17:14.167
YES. I SEE.

17:14.201 --> 17:16.636
WE'LL CONTINUE
THIS CONVERSATION LATER?

17:17.137 --> 17:18.738
ALL RIGHT.

17:19.972 --> 17:22.909
[BARKING]

18:15.828 --> 18:17.764
YOU DIDN'T CLOSE THE DEAL?

18:17.797 --> 18:19.766
THEY'RE WATCHING.

18:19.799 --> 18:21.234
OF COURSE.

18:21.268 --> 18:23.570
CAMERA'S AT 11 O'CLOCK.

18:23.603 --> 18:26.373
[LAUGHING]

18:27.840 --> 18:28.975
[RADIO PLAYS SALSA MUSIC]

18:29.008 --> 18:30.510
THERE.
SALSA.

18:30.543 --> 18:32.111
NOT ME, NO.

18:32.145 --> 18:33.780
FAKE IT.

18:35.348 --> 18:37.016
SO, I DID MY JOB TODAY.

18:37.049 --> 18:40.019
MM. THE STORY
ABOUT OLIVOS?

18:40.052 --> 18:41.354
GUTSY.
YEAH?

18:41.388 --> 18:44.291
WORKED, DIDN'T IT?

18:49.229 --> 18:50.663
IF YOU EVER GET HIM ALONE.

18:50.697 --> 18:53.466
WELL...
THAT'S MY PROBLEM.

18:53.500 --> 18:55.368
YEAH? WHAT ABOUT
OUR PROBLEM?

18:55.402 --> 18:56.936
AND THAT IS?

18:56.969 --> 19:00.307
WELL, IF WE CAN
NEVER BE ALONE

19:00.340 --> 19:05.845
THEN WE NEED TO ACT
MORE NATURAL.

19:08.548 --> 19:10.217
TOGETHER.

19:11.651 --> 19:14.421
HUSBAND AND WIFE.

19:15.655 --> 19:18.525
DAY AND NIGHT.

19:51.891 --> 19:54.026
THERE YOU ARE!

19:54.060 --> 19:55.194
YOU READY
TO LEAVE SO SOON?

19:55.228 --> 19:57.930
OH, LISTEN TO YOU.
I SAW YOU WORKING
THE ROOM WITH NEIL.

19:57.964 --> 20:01.868
YOU SAW NEIL
WORKING THE ROOM.
I WAS RIDING SHOTGUN.

20:01.901 --> 20:03.236
OH, FOLLOWING ORDERS?
EXACTLY.

20:03.270 --> 20:07.240
CHARLOTTE, CAN I BORROW
YOUR HUSBAND ONE MORE MINUTE?

20:07.274 --> 20:08.275
OF COURSE.

20:08.308 --> 20:10.042
DON'T OVERSTAY
YOUR WELCOME, DARLING.

20:10.076 --> 20:12.144
WE WANT TO BE INVITED BACK.

20:13.646 --> 20:14.881
TOM, WE HAVE
A LITTLE SITUATION.

20:14.914 --> 20:17.517
I JUST GOT A CALL
FROM A REPORTER AT
THE WASHINGTON POST.

20:17.550 --> 20:19.552
THEY WANT TO CORROBORATE
A LEAK THEY GOT

20:19.586 --> 20:20.920
ABOUT OUR LITTLE
SITUATION DOWN SOUTH.

20:20.953 --> 20:23.456
HOW THE--
THEY'RE RUNNING
WITH THE STORY

20:23.490 --> 20:24.757
TOMORROW MORNING.

20:24.791 --> 20:26.626
COVERT MISSION.
HIT SQUADS. IT'S UGLY.

20:26.659 --> 20:27.794
I GOTTA CALL
INTO THE VICE PRESIDENT.

20:27.827 --> 20:31.097
IN THE MEANTIME, WE'LL ISSUE
THE STANDARD DENIALS

20:31.130 --> 20:33.099
AND HOPE THEY'RE WEAK
ON THE FACTS.

20:33.132 --> 20:34.301
YOU GOTTA STOP THE STORY.

20:34.334 --> 20:36.102
TOM, I DON'T HAVE
A LEASH ON THE EDITORS
OF THE POST.

20:36.135 --> 20:41.374
I'VE GOT A MAN IN REALE'S
COMPOUND UNDERCOVER RIGHT NOW.

20:41.408 --> 20:43.576
THAT STORY
WILL GET HIM KILLED.

20:43.610 --> 20:47.680
THAT'S WHY THEY CALL IT
A FREE PRESS.

20:57.624 --> 20:58.891
LEAVE IT ON...

20:58.925 --> 21:03.129
ROHAN OR WHATEVER
YOUR NAME IS.

21:03.162 --> 21:04.130
YES.

21:04.163 --> 21:07.133
WHO SLEEPS IN YOUR
BED AT HOME?

21:07.934 --> 21:10.470
MY WIFE.

21:11.438 --> 21:14.674
EVERYBODY
NEEDS A CHANGE.

21:15.007 --> 21:16.609
MAYBE I'LL GO
BACK WITH YOU.

21:16.643 --> 21:18.645
LOOK, MY ORDERS ARE
TO GET YOU SAFELY--

21:18.678 --> 21:23.350
DO YOU THINK
THAT I WOULD LIKE
LIVING IN THE STATES?

21:23.383 --> 21:25.685
[SIGHS]

21:25.718 --> 21:26.486
MARIANA.

21:26.519 --> 21:28.187
BELIEVE ME. I AM
SICK OF THIS COUNTRY

21:28.220 --> 21:29.489
AND I'M SICK
OF THE AGENCY.

21:29.522 --> 21:30.623
AND YOU COULD HELP ME.

21:30.657 --> 21:32.592
I'M A SOLDIER...

21:32.625 --> 21:33.926
NOT A LIFE COACH.

21:33.960 --> 21:36.363
SAY YOU'LL TRY.

21:37.497 --> 21:39.799
SAY YOU'LL TRY.

21:41.167 --> 21:43.002
LOOK...

21:44.337 --> 21:47.006
[MEN YELLING IN SPANISH]

22:01.020 --> 22:03.222
[GUNSHOT]

22:04.424 --> 22:07.026
WHAT THE HELL?

22:15.101 --> 22:17.670
I AM VERY SORRY ABOUT
THE DISTURBANCE.

22:17.704 --> 22:19.372
A MAN HAS BEEN SHOT.

22:19.406 --> 22:20.473
MY GUARDS ARE JUMPY.

22:20.507 --> 22:22.875
THE AMERICAN MEDIA
IS REPORTING A PLOT
TO ASSASSINATE

22:22.909 --> 22:24.811
AN OFFICIAL
OF MY COUNTRY.

22:24.844 --> 22:27.647
THAT, MOST PROBABLY,
WOULD BE ME.

22:27.680 --> 22:29.048
OH, MY GOD.

22:29.081 --> 22:30.316
HOW IS
YOUR SECURITY?

22:30.349 --> 22:32.819
THE NATIONAL POLICE
ARE ALREADY
PATROLLING THE AREA.

22:32.852 --> 22:35.321
THE MAN
THEY JUST SHOT--

22:35.354 --> 22:36.823
IS HE AN AMERICAN?

22:36.856 --> 22:39.025
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT HE WAS.

22:39.058 --> 22:40.993
BUT HE NO LONGER
IS MY PROBLEM.

22:41.027 --> 22:41.761
WE SHOULD LEAVE.

22:41.794 --> 22:43.596
FOR NOW, YOU WOULD
BE SAFER HERE.

22:43.630 --> 22:44.931
I DON'T KNOW.

22:44.964 --> 22:45.898
I KNOW. PLEASE.

22:45.932 --> 22:49.001
WE MUST NOT LET THEM
INTERFERE WITH OUR PLANS.

22:49.035 --> 22:52.939
ACCEPT MY HOSPITALITY
AND MY PROTECTION.

22:52.972 --> 22:54.807
PLEASE.

22:58.778 --> 23:01.047
IT HAD BETTER WORK.

23:13.826 --> 23:16.563
AND HOW WAS YOUR DAY?

23:27.306 --> 23:28.841
[GRUNTS]

23:33.112 --> 23:35.114
DIRT DIVER,
THIS IS DOG PATCH.

23:35.147 --> 23:37.617
WE GOT GALE WARNINGS ISSUED
FOR YOUR AREA.

23:37.650 --> 23:40.119
DOG PATCH,
WE HAVE RECEIVED
THE WEATHER ALERT.

23:40.152 --> 23:41.488
WE ARE ON LOOKOUT.

23:41.521 --> 23:43.623
WE MAY HAVE TO CANCEL
THE WHOLE FISHING TRIP.

23:43.656 --> 23:44.557
BE A DAMN SHAME.

23:44.591 --> 23:46.793
WE'D SURE LIKE
TO REEL IN THE BIG ONE.

23:46.826 --> 23:48.294
COOL BREEZE ON SHORE
WILL HELP WITH THAT.

23:48.327 --> 23:51.063
SIR, WE HAVE HAD
NO REPORT OF
COOL BREEZE TODAY.

23:51.097 --> 23:52.064
HE MISSED
HIS COMMO WINDOW?

23:52.098 --> 23:54.667
ROGER THAT.
ADVISE WE CONTACT
SNAKE DOCTOR?

23:54.701 --> 23:58.104
NEGATIVE. CONTACT
WITH SNAKE DOC IS
BY EXCEPTION ONLY.

23:58.137 --> 24:00.006
I SAY AGAIN,
BY EXCEPTION ONLY.

24:00.039 --> 24:02.408
WHEN AND IF
HE NEEDS TO CUT BAIT.

24:02.441 --> 24:06.345
ROGER THAT.
WE'LL KEEP TRYING
COOL BREEZE.

24:06.378 --> 24:08.114
[BEEPS]

24:08.147 --> 24:09.649
[HONKS]

24:09.682 --> 24:11.083
[LAUGHS]
WANT TO RIDE?

24:11.117 --> 24:13.620
CRYSTAL! WHAT IS THIS?

24:13.653 --> 24:14.487
COME ON, ONCE
AROUND THE BLOCK.

24:14.521 --> 24:18.758
I CAN'T. TEDDY'S ASLEEP.
WHERE DID YOU--

24:18.791 --> 24:19.626
ROCKS, HUH?

24:19.659 --> 24:22.695
IT'S PRETTY FLASHY, YEAH.

24:22.729 --> 24:23.596
I LIKE IT.

24:23.630 --> 24:25.264
JEREMY'S GOING TO FLIP.

24:25.297 --> 24:26.799
THAT'S GREAT, CRYSTAL.

24:26.833 --> 24:28.735
OH!

24:29.001 --> 24:30.469
I GOT YOU
SOMETHING, TOO.

24:30.503 --> 24:32.338
ME? WHY ME?

24:32.371 --> 24:33.472
I WANTED TO, IS ALL.

24:33.506 --> 24:34.841
YOU'VE BEEN SO SWEET
TO JEREMY AND ME,

24:34.874 --> 24:38.010
AND I KNOW
YOU'RE GOING
TO LOVE IT.

24:39.011 --> 24:39.646
LORD.

24:39.679 --> 24:40.813
WELL, I KNOW HOW
YOU'RE INTO

24:40.847 --> 24:43.149
TAKING PICTURES
OF THE KIDS, AND--

24:43.182 --> 24:44.517
WELL, I AM, BUT--

24:44.551 --> 24:46.553
YOU GOT THAT
GORGEOUS BABY NOW.

24:46.586 --> 24:48.120
DON'T TEDDY DESERVE
THE BEST?

24:48.154 --> 24:51.157
THIS IS
A LAVISH GIFT,
CRYSTAL.

24:51.190 --> 24:53.593
YES, IT IS.

24:54.927 --> 24:57.930
THANK YOU, HONEY.

24:58.330 --> 25:00.299
SHE'S JUST YOUNG.
ISN'T THAT WHAT
YOU TOLD ME?

25:00.332 --> 25:03.002
SHE IS. BUT NOW
SHE'S FOOLISH, TOO.

25:03.035 --> 25:04.971
I MEAN, JEREMY'S
MAKING MONEY
AT BLACKTHORNE,

25:05.004 --> 25:08.140
BUT IT CAN'T BE
THAT MUCH. CAN IT?

25:08.174 --> 25:09.842
YOU KNOW I CAN'T
TELL YOU THAT.

25:09.876 --> 25:11.744
SHE MUST'VE SPENT
A FORTUNE ON THAT CAR.

25:11.778 --> 25:12.979
THAT'S JUST IMPULSIVE.

25:13.012 --> 25:14.714
I AM JUST TRYING
TO LOOK OUT FOR HER.

25:14.747 --> 25:17.149
AND NOW YOU WANT ME
TO TAKE ON THAT ROLE.

25:17.183 --> 25:18.685
YOU RECRUITED THEM.

25:18.718 --> 25:20.687
[DOORBELL RINGS]

25:25.524 --> 25:27.493
BEVERLY. HELLO.

25:27.526 --> 25:28.527
HOW ARE YOU, MOLLY?

25:28.561 --> 25:29.929
I'M WELL.
VERY WELL.

25:29.962 --> 25:31.197
I JUST WANTED
TO BRING YOU THIS.

25:31.230 --> 25:32.932
SAFER HERE
THAN AT MY SHOP.

25:32.965 --> 25:34.601
IT'S A BEAUTIFUL RING.

25:34.634 --> 25:37.136
THANK YOU.

25:37.536 --> 25:39.438
WOULD YOU LIKE
TO COME IN?

25:39.471 --> 25:42.074
NO. I SHOULD BE
GETTING BACK TO WORK.

25:42.108 --> 25:44.577
OFF YOU GO, THEN.

25:44.611 --> 25:46.713
OK.

25:55.988 --> 25:57.590
CONGRESSMAN,
YOU GOT A MINUTE?

25:57.624 --> 25:58.357
COLONEL.

25:58.390 --> 25:59.291
WE NEED TO TALK,
YOU AND ME.

25:59.325 --> 26:00.459
OH, NOT RIGHT NOW.
I'M IN CONFERENCE.

26:00.492 --> 26:02.294
CAROL, GET
THE COLONEL'S NUMBER AND--

26:02.328 --> 26:04.731
NO, SIR.

26:04.764 --> 26:06.799
IT NEEDS TO BE NOW.

26:08.334 --> 26:09.969
ALL RIGHT.
WHAT'S ON YOUR MIND?

26:10.002 --> 26:11.738
YOUR ACTIONS
PUT MY MEN AND
MY MISSION AT RISK.

26:11.771 --> 26:14.707
YOUR ACTIONS PUT
THIS COUNTRY'S FOREIGN
RELATIONS AT RISK.

26:14.741 --> 26:15.875
I TOLD YOU,
THAT WAS NOT MY LOOKOUT.

26:15.908 --> 26:18.110
THE HELL IT AIN'T,
SOLDIER AND YOU KNOW
BETTER THAN THAT.

26:18.144 --> 26:19.111
NO, I'LL TELL YOU
WHAT I KNOW.

26:19.145 --> 26:21.113
YOU LEAKED CLASSIFIED
INFORMATION TO THE PAPERS,

26:21.147 --> 26:23.115
AND I HAVE 5 MEN
IN IT UP TO THEIR ASS.

26:23.149 --> 26:26.619
AS A FORMER SOLDIER,
I UNDERSTAND
YOUR CONCERN. I DO.

26:26.653 --> 26:29.889
BUT THIS IS MUCH BIGGER
THAN YOUR 5 MEN,
COLONEL.

26:29.922 --> 26:30.957
THEN YOU SHOULD'VE
TAKEN THAT UP

26:30.990 --> 26:33.592
WITH NEIL KRINSMAN
AND HIS BOYS AT
THE WHITE HOUSE.

26:33.626 --> 26:34.661
THOSE BED-WETTERS?

26:34.694 --> 26:36.963
THEY'RE MIGHTY QUICK
TO PUT YOUR BOYS
IN HARM'S WAY,

26:36.996 --> 26:40.299
BUT THERE'S NOT
A ONE OF THEM EVER
SERVED A DAY IN UNIFORM.

26:40.332 --> 26:41.968
I STILL HAVE
A MISSION TO COMPLETE.

26:42.001 --> 26:43.636
WELL, ASK YOURSELF FIRST

26:43.670 --> 26:46.839
WHO REALLY STANDS
TO GAIN IF REALE DIES.

26:46.873 --> 26:51.277
IT'S NOT GEOPOLITICS,
MY FRIEND. IT'S OIL.

26:51.310 --> 26:53.780
REALE IS SQUEEZING
THE OIL COMPANIES,

26:53.813 --> 26:55.581
CUTTING INTO
THEIR WINDFALL PROFITS.

26:55.614 --> 26:59.786
THAT'S WHO YOUR BOYS
ARE FIGHTING FOR
ON THIS ONE--

26:59.819 --> 27:01.654
BIG OIL.

27:01.688 --> 27:04.490
I PRAY
THEY GET OUT SAFELY.

27:05.024 --> 27:07.359
GOOD LUCK TO YOU.

27:13.666 --> 27:16.102
WHAT WERE YOU DOING
OUT THERE?

27:16.135 --> 27:17.236
BIRDING.
BIRDING?

27:17.269 --> 27:19.438
I'M AN ORNITHOLOGIST
FROM THE UNIVERSITY
OF MANITOBA--

27:19.471 --> 27:20.372
YOU ARE AMERICAN!

27:20.406 --> 27:21.273
NO, I'M NOT AN AMERICAN.
LOOK AT MY PASSPORT.

27:21.307 --> 27:22.875
I'M CANADIAN.
YOUR PASSPORT'S A LIE!

27:22.909 --> 27:23.743
YOU'RE C.I.A.!

27:23.776 --> 27:24.977
PLEASE, PLEASE!
JUST CALL
THE EMBASSY.

27:25.011 --> 27:27.313
I'LL SHOOT OUT
YOUR BRAINS IF I PLEASE.

27:27.346 --> 27:29.548
CALL THE CANADIAN
EMBASSY--

27:30.016 --> 27:31.818
WHERE ARE THE OTHERS?

27:31.851 --> 27:32.885
WE KNOW
THERE ARE OTHERS!

27:32.919 --> 27:35.187
LOOK,
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

27:39.491 --> 27:40.960
WE WILL FIND
THE OTHERS.

27:40.993 --> 27:42.394
AND YOU ARE GOING
TO BE HERE

27:42.428 --> 27:45.364
ON A VERY, VERY
LONG VACATION.

27:57.376 --> 27:58.745
SHE HAS GREAT FORM.

27:58.778 --> 28:00.312
SHE DOES, THAT.

28:00.346 --> 28:02.882
SHE IS GOOD FOR YOU.
I CAN TELL.

28:02.915 --> 28:04.316
[CHUCKLES]

28:04.350 --> 28:05.617
LUIS...

28:05.651 --> 28:08.587
I WOULD LIKE TO FINISH
THE CONVERSATION WE WERE
HAVING LAST NIGHT.

28:08.620 --> 28:09.588
IN PRIVATE.

28:09.621 --> 28:11.523
YOU HAVE BEEN MARRIED
6 YEARS?

28:11.557 --> 28:12.725
YES.

28:12.759 --> 28:14.360
THAT IS WHAT
KEEPS ME THINKING...

28:14.393 --> 28:15.527
MY MARRIAGE?

28:15.561 --> 28:16.695
OLIVOS.
AS I REMEMBER,

28:16.729 --> 28:19.431
THE ONLY AVOCADO ORCHARD
WAS OWNED BY
THE RAMIREZ FAMILY,

28:19.465 --> 28:22.501
AND IT WAS TAKEN OVER
BY THE GENERALS

28:22.534 --> 28:24.236
7 YEARS AGO.

28:24.270 --> 28:26.672
HOW COULD YOU
HAVE MARRIED THERE?

28:26.705 --> 28:30.777
MARIANA'S FAMILY.
THEY HAD A FRIEND.

28:30.810 --> 28:34.914
FRIENDS WITH THE JUNTA?
WITH FASCISTS?

28:34.947 --> 28:36.548
CERTAINLY NOT.

28:36.582 --> 28:38.617
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

28:38.650 --> 28:41.754
HE'S JUST TRYING
TO BE POLITE.

28:41.788 --> 28:44.123
MY FATHER WAS
A SIMPLE GARDENER.

28:44.156 --> 28:49.128
MANY YEARS HE WORKED
THE ORCHARDS FOR
THE RAMIREZ FAMILY.

28:49.161 --> 28:51.964
AND WHEN THE GENERAL
TOOK OVER,

28:51.998 --> 28:54.200
HE WAS FORCED TO
WORK WITH THEM, TOO.

28:54.233 --> 28:55.802
POBRECITO.

28:55.835 --> 28:57.703
SO, AS A GESTURE
OF KINDNESS,

28:57.736 --> 29:00.406
THEY LET
HIS DAUGHTER BE
MARRIED THERE.

29:00.439 --> 29:02.274
FORGIVE ROHAN HIS PRIDE.

29:02.308 --> 29:05.111
YOU KNOW, A GARDENER
FOR A FATHER-IN-LAW.

29:05.144 --> 29:08.480
THERE IS NO SHAME
IN WORKING WITH
YOUR HANDS.

29:08.514 --> 29:10.149
DON'T FORGET THAT,
ROHAN.

29:10.182 --> 29:13.252
NO SIR. I WILL NOT.

29:16.255 --> 29:17.489
I BELIEVE
THIS IS A FIGHT

29:17.523 --> 29:18.590
BETWEEN THE WHITE HOUSE
AND CONGRESS,

29:18.624 --> 29:21.293
AND I DON'T THINK
YOU WANT TO BE
THE CROSSING GUARD.

29:21.327 --> 29:22.494
ISN'T THAT
WHERE I AM?

29:22.528 --> 29:24.897
DECLINE
THE POSITION.

29:24.931 --> 29:25.832
I'M LISTENING.

29:25.865 --> 29:27.800
THE BETTER MOVE
IS TO GO TO
GELBER'S CHAIR

29:27.834 --> 29:29.268
AND BRING HIM
SOMETHING.

29:29.301 --> 29:30.136
AND BRING HIM WHAT?

29:30.169 --> 29:31.303
SOMETHING SO HE CAN LOOK
AT YOU AND SAY,

29:31.337 --> 29:32.338
"THAT MAN DID
SOMETHING FOR ME."

29:32.371 --> 29:33.439
ISN'T THAT THE WAY
THE WORLD WORKS?

29:33.472 --> 29:36.475
YOU WANT ME
TO GO TO THE CHAIR
OF GELBER'S COMMITTEE.

29:36.508 --> 29:37.609
THAT'S RIGHT.

29:37.643 --> 29:38.945
AND BRING HIM WHAT?

29:38.978 --> 29:40.346
EYES-ONLY MEMOS.
OPERATIONAL DOCUMENTS.

29:40.379 --> 29:43.615
AND THEN HE BLOCKS
GELBER'S PROBE
IN COMMITTEE.

29:43.649 --> 29:44.450
WELL...

29:44.483 --> 29:45.617
DO PEOPLE GET HURT
ON THE BATTLEFIELD?

29:45.651 --> 29:47.786
THEY GET HURT
HERE, TOO--

29:47.820 --> 29:49.588
WHO DO YOU THINK
YOU'RE DEALING WITH?

29:49.621 --> 29:51.290
I THINK, THOUGH
YOU DIDN'T ASK,

29:51.323 --> 29:54.093
THAT YOU SHOULD
TAKE TILL MONDAY,
AND LET IT COOL DOWN.

29:54.126 --> 29:55.094
TILL MONDAY?
YES.

29:55.127 --> 29:56.996
MY MEN ARE
IN CONTACT NOW.

29:57.029 --> 29:57.930
I UNDERSTAND.
BUT CONSIDER--

29:57.964 --> 30:00.099
IF YOU ANGER KRINSMAN,
YOU ANGER HIS BETTERS.

30:00.132 --> 30:01.968
WHICH IS TO SAY,
YOU ANGER THE THRONE.

30:02.001 --> 30:03.635
WHICH IS THE END OF YOU.
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

30:03.669 --> 30:06.005
AND THEN WHAT HAPPENS
TO YOUR MEN?

30:06.038 --> 30:07.840
[RING]

30:08.674 --> 30:09.976
[RING]

30:10.009 --> 30:11.443
[BEEPS]

30:11.477 --> 30:13.679
YEAH? GO.

30:14.046 --> 30:16.148
HE MISSED
HIS SECOND WINDOW?

30:16.182 --> 30:17.649
WHAT ABOUT THE REST
OF THE UNIT?

30:17.683 --> 30:21.453
ALL RIGHT.
HAVE DIRT DIVER
MOVE ASHORE.

30:21.487 --> 30:24.023
IS EVERYTHING OK?

30:24.056 --> 30:26.725
NOT BY A LONG SHOT.

30:33.532 --> 30:36.168
YOU LIKE BIRDS?

30:37.336 --> 30:39.238
PAJAROS?

30:40.039 --> 30:42.174
YEAH.

30:42.942 --> 30:45.677
HAVE YOU EVER SEEN
A BLUE-FOOTED BOOBY?

30:45.711 --> 30:46.879
HUH?

30:46.913 --> 30:49.949
OH, IT'S--
IT'S IN THERE.

30:50.182 --> 30:52.751
IT HAS A VERY
DISTINCTIVE, UM--

30:54.186 --> 30:55.821
[CHUCKLES]

30:55.854 --> 30:58.557
[IMITATING BIRD CALL]

30:59.358 --> 31:01.427
IT'S THERE.
I'LL SHOW YOU
IN THAT BOOK.

31:01.460 --> 31:03.095
NO, NO, NO.
IT'S OK.

31:03.129 --> 31:05.464
I'M JUST, UM--

31:06.198 --> 31:08.734
BLUE FOOTED BOOBY.

31:08.767 --> 31:10.069
IT'S--IT'S A RARITY.

31:10.102 --> 31:13.772
AND YOU'RE LUCKY
TO HAVE HERE
IN YOUR COMPANY.

31:13.805 --> 31:18.510
I'LL--I'LL--
I'LL SHOW IT TO YOU.

31:18.544 --> 31:20.679
YEAH? LOOK.

31:20.712 --> 31:22.481
[GRUNTING]

31:23.415 --> 31:25.717
[KEYS CLINKING]

31:35.661 --> 31:37.263
YOU'RE KIDDING ME,
RIGHT?

31:37.296 --> 31:37.964
NO, SIR.

31:37.997 --> 31:39.065
YOU WANT
THE VICE PRESIDENT

31:39.098 --> 31:40.066
TO PUT HIS NAME
ON THIS MISSION?

31:40.099 --> 31:42.434
TOM, IF YOU'RE CONCERNED
ABOUT LEAKS--

31:42.468 --> 31:43.469
THE MISSION.

31:43.502 --> 31:45.904
IF THEY EVER LAUNCH
AN INVESTIGATION
OF MY UNIT,

31:45.938 --> 31:47.639
I WANT TO MAKE SURE
YOU GOT MY BACK.

31:47.673 --> 31:48.975
I STAND BEHIND YOU
AND THIS MISSION.

31:49.008 --> 31:51.043
I KNOW THE VEEP FEELS
THE SAME WAY.

31:51.077 --> 31:53.412
THEN LET HIM SAY SO
IN WRITING.

31:54.146 --> 31:55.447
SOMEONE GOT TO YOU.

31:55.481 --> 31:57.049
I NEED THE SIGNATURE.

31:57.083 --> 31:58.217
I GUESS I HAD YOU
PEGGED WRONG.

31:58.250 --> 32:01.087
I FIGURED YOU FOR
ONE OF OUR CAN-DO GUYS.

32:01.120 --> 32:02.821
DO I ABORT THE MISSION?

32:02.854 --> 32:04.790
LET'S NOT PRETEND HERE.

32:04.823 --> 32:07.659
YOU AND I BOTH KNOW
HOW IT WORKS.
WE MANAGE UP.

32:07.693 --> 32:09.928
OUR JOB IS TO PROTECT
THE PEOPLE WE WORK FOR.

32:09.962 --> 32:13.632
AND HERE
I THOUGHT OUR JOB WAS
TO PROTECT THE COUNTRY.

32:13.665 --> 32:14.900
OH, DON'T PULL
THAT CRAP WITH ME.

32:14.933 --> 32:18.237
I DID 3 TERMS ON
THE HOUSE SUB-COMMITTEE
FOR MILITARY AFFAIRS.

32:18.270 --> 32:19.338
CONGRESSMAN REYNOLDS,
RIGHT?

32:19.371 --> 32:21.273
MIDLAND, TEXAS,
WASN'T IT?
ELEVENTH DISTRICT.

32:21.307 --> 32:23.175
THAT IS CORRECT.
ANY OIL IN THOSE PARTS?

32:23.209 --> 32:24.443
WHAT'S THAT SUPPOSED
TO MEAN?

32:24.476 --> 32:29.281
LET'S JUST SAY
I LIKE TO KNOW
WHO I WORK FOR.

32:34.220 --> 32:35.121
[DOOR CLOSES]

32:35.154 --> 32:38.624
MOLLY, EVERYTHING OK HERE?
SANDWICH GOOD?

32:38.657 --> 32:41.793
IT'S ALL FINE, THANKS.
HOW ARE YOU, BABY?

32:41.827 --> 32:43.829
BESIDES THE BLISTERED FEET
AND CHIPPED NAILS?

32:43.862 --> 32:47.299
COUPLE MORE OF JEREMY'S GIGS,
I'M GOING TO OWN THIS PLACE.

32:47.333 --> 32:50.536
KIM TOLD ME ABOUT
YOUR NEW CAR.
I'M HAPPY FOR YOU.

32:50.569 --> 32:52.204
YEAH? THANKS.

32:52.238 --> 32:57.276
CRYSTAL, I DON'T
WANT TO GET
INTO YOUR AFFAIRS--

32:57.309 --> 32:58.344
THEN WHY ARE YOU HERE?

32:58.377 --> 33:01.813
KIM IS LITTLE CONCERNED--
AS ARE THE REST OF US--

33:01.847 --> 33:04.616
THAT PERHAPS YOU ARE
A BIT OVER-EXUBERANT

33:04.650 --> 33:06.852
WITH YOUR NEWFOUND
MONEY.

33:07.653 --> 33:09.788
IS IT MY MONEY?

33:09.821 --> 33:12.491
HONEY, DON'T GET UPSET.

33:15.494 --> 33:18.230
HOW DO YOU DO THIS?

33:18.264 --> 33:20.032
HOW DO YOU GET UP
EVERY MORNING

33:20.066 --> 33:22.234
AND NOT THINK ABOUT
WHERE HE IS,

33:22.268 --> 33:23.835
WHAT HE'S DOING,
IF HE'S OK?!

33:23.869 --> 33:26.004
OR IF HE'S EVEN
THINKING ABOUT YOU?

33:26.038 --> 33:28.974
COULD HE CARE LESS
THAT I BOUGHT
15 PAIRS OF SHOES

33:29.007 --> 33:29.875
OR SOME STUPID NEW CAR?

33:29.908 --> 33:32.511
MAYBE HE'S OUT GETTING
LOADED EVERY NIGHT,

33:32.544 --> 33:34.180
OR MAYBE HE'S SHACKING UP
WITH SOME OTHER GIRL.

33:34.213 --> 33:40.686
MAYBE HE'S LAYING
DEAD ON THE SIDE
OF A DESERT ROAD.

33:41.053 --> 33:44.690
HOW DO YOU NOT THINK
ABOUT THOSE THINGS?

33:46.125 --> 33:48.860
I DON'T GO THERE.

33:49.628 --> 33:51.330
THAT'S IT?

33:51.363 --> 33:54.900
THAT'S THE WISDOM
OF A CAREER ARMY WIFE--

33:54.933 --> 33:57.769
"DON'T GO THERE"?

34:03.575 --> 34:06.112
PULL!

34:07.479 --> 34:09.448
BE AHEAD
OF YOUR TARGET.

34:09.481 --> 34:12.251
I AM NOT MUCH
FOR GUNS, I'M AFRAID.

34:12.284 --> 34:14.720
WATCH.

34:19.391 --> 34:21.460
BRUJA, PULL.

34:21.493 --> 34:24.096
[GUNSHOTS]

34:27.166 --> 34:29.968
IMPRESSIVE.

34:30.001 --> 34:32.204
THE AMERICANS
BETTER WATCH OUT, EH?

34:32.238 --> 34:34.806
I DON'T THINK
YOU HAVE TO
WORRY ABOUT THEM.

34:34.840 --> 34:36.708
THEY WANT ME,
THEY'LL GET ME.

34:36.742 --> 34:39.711
DROP A 500 POUND
BOMB ON MY HEAD.

34:39.745 --> 34:40.846
WELL, NOT TODAY,
I HOPE.

34:40.879 --> 34:45.484
AND TURN MEN INTO MARTYRS,
ISN'T THAT WHAT THEY DO BEST?

34:45.917 --> 34:48.920
TO BE HONEST,
I HAVE LITTLE USE
FOR IMMORTALITY.

34:48.954 --> 34:52.158
WHAT IS IMPORTANT TO ME...

34:53.359 --> 34:54.160
ALL RIGHT.

34:54.193 --> 34:57.329
I JUST WANT TO DO RIGHT
BY MY PEOPLE.

34:58.530 --> 35:02.501
LET'S WALK
AND WE'LL CONCLUDE
OUR BUSINESS.

35:02.534 --> 35:04.570
[CELL PHONE RINGS]
OH!

35:04.603 --> 35:06.572
OH, EXCUSE ME.

35:06.605 --> 35:09.441
MY CLIENT.

35:09.475 --> 35:10.976
YES?

35:11.009 --> 35:12.778
NEGOTIATIONS
STILL ONGOING?

35:12.811 --> 35:13.679
YES.

35:13.712 --> 35:14.980
AS WE SPEAK.

35:15.013 --> 35:16.682
THEN STOP.
DEAL IS OFF.

35:16.715 --> 35:18.116
CONFIRM THAT?

35:18.150 --> 35:20.786
DEAL IS OFF.
TERMS HAVE CHANGED.

35:20.819 --> 35:22.788
OH, IS THAT NOT SOMETHING?

35:22.821 --> 35:25.524
I'LL FILL YOU IN LATER.
GO ON, SET SAIL

35:25.557 --> 35:27.593
WHILE COOL BREEZE
IS AT YOUR BACK.

35:27.626 --> 35:29.828
THIS I WILL DO.

35:29.861 --> 35:32.464
[CLICK]

35:32.498 --> 35:34.300
I APOLOGIZE, GENTLEMEN.

35:34.333 --> 35:36.202
I HAVE SOME
UNFORTUNATE NEWS--

35:36.235 --> 35:38.337
[COCKS GUN]

35:38.370 --> 35:42.508
YOU SHOULD HAVE SHOT ME
WHEN YOU HAD THE CHANCE.

35:47.513 --> 35:50.816
YOU ARE THE ASSASSIN.

35:51.350 --> 35:52.651
I'M AFRAID NOT.

35:52.684 --> 35:54.553
YOU MAY BE A POOR SHOT TODAY,

35:54.586 --> 35:57.155
BUT YOU HAVE
HANDLED GUNS BEFORE.

35:57.189 --> 35:59.024
THE MUZZLE.

35:59.057 --> 36:00.692
BEGINNERS ARE
NEVER SO CAREFUL.

36:00.726 --> 36:01.993
YOU WEREN'T CLUMSY ENOUGH.

36:02.027 --> 36:03.862
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING
ABOUT, LUIS.

36:03.895 --> 36:05.163
YOU GOT CAJONES,
MY FRIEND.

36:05.197 --> 36:10.469
YOU COME INTO MY HOUSE,
DRINK MY LIQUOR,
EAT MY FOOD?

36:10.502 --> 36:13.004
WOULD YOU LIKE TO PRAY?

36:13.038 --> 36:14.873
WOULD YOU LIKE TO PRAY?

36:14.906 --> 36:18.910
BUT WHAT WOULD I PRAY
FOR? A NEW PUPPY?

36:18.944 --> 36:20.579
ROHAN!

36:21.513 --> 36:24.550
[COCKS GUN]
GO AHEAD. DO IT.

36:24.583 --> 36:26.252
KILL HIM.
LET'S GO.

36:26.285 --> 36:28.820
KILL HIM ALREADY!
LET'S GO.

36:28.854 --> 36:31.189
RUN! RUN NOW!

36:38.063 --> 36:40.932
STAY OFF THE ROADS.
THEY'LL BE LOOKING FOR YOU.

36:40.966 --> 36:42.534
FOLLOW THE RAT LINE.
AND YOU?

36:42.568 --> 36:44.102
I'M YOUR DECOY.

36:44.135 --> 36:47.205
SEE YOU ON BOARD.
YEP.

37:00.286 --> 37:02.153
OH, NO...

37:07.659 --> 37:09.194
ALL RIGHT,
SPREAD YOUR LEGS.

37:09.227 --> 37:12.431
IF YOU THINK
I'M GONNA GO DOWN THERE...

37:12.464 --> 37:14.466
WHAT, YOU WANT
TO GO BACK TO THE VILLA?

37:14.500 --> 37:19.438
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.
I CAN'T.

37:19.471 --> 37:22.107
[SIGHS]

37:22.140 --> 37:23.141
ALL RIGHT.

37:23.174 --> 37:24.242
I'M GONNA DO
SOMETHING

37:24.276 --> 37:25.711
THAT'S GONNA MAKE IT
FEEL BETTER FOR YOU.

37:25.744 --> 37:29.781
I'M GONNA TAKE YOU
DOWN ON MY BACK.

37:32.017 --> 37:33.752
TRUST ME.

37:58.009 --> 37:59.511
ALL RIGHT.

37:59.545 --> 38:02.548
LATCH IT ON
TO THE BELT.

38:03.482 --> 38:05.283
GET ON MY BACK.

38:05.317 --> 38:08.053
YEAH, YOU'RE GOOD?
YEAH.

38:51.863 --> 38:54.332
[SIREN]

38:54.366 --> 38:56.067
[GUNSHOTS]

38:56.101 --> 38:58.904
[SCREAMING]

39:02.608 --> 39:05.010
[GRUNTS]

39:08.780 --> 39:10.849
[GRUNTS]

39:14.520 --> 39:16.688
GO!

39:28.800 --> 39:30.802
AHH!

39:41.547 --> 39:43.782
GOT HER IN THE ARM.

39:47.553 --> 39:49.788
AH!

40:06.104 --> 40:07.606
OK. YOU'RE OK.

40:07.639 --> 40:10.909
WE'RE GONNA GET
YOUR ARM FIXED UP.

40:22.120 --> 40:23.121
THIS WON'T TAKE
5 MINUTES.

40:23.154 --> 40:25.323
I JUST NEED
TO SIGN OFF ON
JEREMY'S HEALTH CARE.

40:25.356 --> 40:30.128
THOUGHT I WAS
BEING CALLED INTO
THE PRINCIPAL'S OFFICE.

40:30.161 --> 40:31.262
DON'T BE SILLY.

40:31.296 --> 40:33.632
IF ANYONE'S AT FAULT,
IT'S ME.

40:33.665 --> 40:35.567
I SHOULDN'T HAVE
UPSET YOU AT WORK.

40:35.601 --> 40:40.005
HAVE A SEAT.
I'LL GET YOUR PAPERWORK.

40:41.873 --> 40:45.944
HELLO? IS THIS THING
WORKING? HELLO?

40:45.977 --> 40:48.580
OH, MY GOD. JEREMY!

40:48.614 --> 40:50.816
CRYSTAL?
CAN YOU HEAR ME?

40:50.849 --> 40:54.786
HI, BABY, I'M HERE!
CAN YOU SEE ME?

40:54.820 --> 40:55.721
YEAH.

40:55.754 --> 41:00.859
HEY, BABY. HOW ARE YOU?
I MISS YOU SO MUCH.

41:00.892 --> 41:03.294
I MISS YOU.

41:03.328 --> 41:05.597
YOU'RE COMING HOME
SOON I HOPE?

41:05.631 --> 41:07.198
WE'RE DONE HERE NEXT WEEK,
THEN I'M BACK.

41:07.232 --> 41:11.369
GOOD, 'CAUSE I GOT YOU
A BIG SURPRISE.

41:11.402 --> 41:12.237
GET OUT.

41:12.270 --> 41:14.506
WELL, I CAN'T WAIT.
I GOT YOU A NEW CAR!

41:14.540 --> 41:17.843
IT'S A KICK-ASS MUSTANG.
IT'S COBALT BLUE,

41:17.876 --> 41:22.447
LEATHER SEATS
AND, CHECK IT, A CONVERTIBLE!

41:22.480 --> 41:25.350
OH, SWEET!

41:26.017 --> 41:27.152
I LOVE YOU, HONEY!

41:27.185 --> 41:31.723
DO YOU LOVE ME?
OR DO YOU JUST LOVE
MY "THOUGHTFULNESS"?

41:31.757 --> 41:34.259
[LAUGHS]

42:05.757 --> 42:08.026
THANK YOU.

42:09.761 --> 42:11.763
FOR BRINGING ME BACK.

42:11.797 --> 42:14.532
HOW YOU FEELING?

42:16.267 --> 42:18.169
BETTER NOW.

42:18.203 --> 42:21.673
MARIANA, MISSION'S OVER.

42:21.707 --> 42:25.143
IT DOESN'T HAVE TO BE.

42:28.313 --> 42:30.716
OH, I UNDERSTAND.
NOT HERE.

42:30.749 --> 42:34.986
NO. NOT AGAIN.

42:38.223 --> 42:41.259
I'M GOING BACK HOME.
TO MY WIFE.

44:08.513 --> 44:10.348
YOU'RE HOME.

44:10.381 --> 44:12.884
HEY, BABY.

44:18.423 --> 44:20.525
COME HERE.
